@sarahcashburger1560 I understand where you’re coming from and there are points I can agree with. But for one, the show’s quality is subjective and doesn’t factor into this argument. You thought the show was bad (I thought it was fine…better than most the other MCU D+ shows) but whether it was good or bad doesn’t determine its continuity across the franchise. Thor TDW was received badly but we still got Thor and the mention of the reality stone. We know Ant man will be in Doomsday despite the third movie being a flop and I know we’ll see Cap Marvel, Rambo, and Miss Marvel again. 

Second, it depends on the scale of plot details that should be considered for continuity across different movies/shows. You’re right, I don’t think they should’ve referenced Hawkeye, She Hulk, or Echo considering the interactions those shows had were small in scale and were personal to Fisk/Murdoc that had to effect on this show. I think it is fine to have standalone stories that aren’t acknowledged in the bigger picture, again depending on the scale. I think all 3 seasons of Netflix DD don’t need to be mentioned in the greater MCU at the time because it was really between Fisk and Murdoc. But, something like Fisk is the mayor of NYC, Fisk is controlling the city with a corrupt hand, and Fisk has enacted a law that bans superheroes and all those that oppose it will be locked up, that’s too big of a scale to not be continuous across other movies. That affects all heroes residing in NYC and if Thunderbolts, Spiderman, Strange, etc have movies that take place in NYC after this show, it should be acknowledged. Especially if Fiege keeps saying everything is connected. 

I get the comics have had plenty of stories where heroes have their own journey disconnected from others’. But this is the MCU, it’s significantly smaller than all of Marvel’s comic runs, and since 2008, everything has been connected. That’s just how it is and if it continues to be (which we haven’t been told otherwise) then certain story plots from this show, like the above mentioned, should be carried into other movies.

